[[File:MaumereBay.jpg|right|150px|thumb|Maumere bay]]
{{coord|-8.62|S|122.22|E|type:city|display=title}}

'''Maumere''' is the largest town of [[Flores]] and the centre of business. It lies on the north coast of the island and the port is in the northwest part of the town. The [[Maumere Airport]] is located in Maumere. As of 1992 Maumere had a total population of 70,000.<ref name=UNDHA>[http://www.reliefweb.int/rw/RWB.NSF/db900SID/OCHA-64BHB5?OpenDocument Reports 1 - 9] ''[[United Nations Department of Humanitarian Affairs]]''</ref>

The town suffered considerable damage in the [[1992 Indonesia earthquake]], with 90 percent of all buildings being destroyed.<ref name=UNDHA/>

In 2005, the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Maumere]] was erected in the town.

The reefs in in areas surrounding Maumere (the Maumere Gulf) were once considered some of the finest diving in the world. However, a 2007 report found that 75% of the [[coral reef]]s had been significantly damaged or destroyed by the practice of [[blast fishing|bomb fishing]], the use [[toxicity|toxic]] chemicals in fishing, and due to [[earthquake]]s. <ref>{{Citation
  | title = SOME 75 PERCENT OF CORAL REEFS IN MAUMERE GULF DAMAGED
  | newspaper = ANT - LKBN ANTARA (Indonesia)
  | year = 2007
  | date = 31-MAY-07
  | url = http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-30918157_ITM}}</ref>

